      "writtenOn": "2017-09-19T07:47:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This `struct` library is standard library of python hence it should added somewhere along 16-18 (alphabetical order). The approach in Openstack is that imports are grouped in 3 chunks:\n\n1) standard library imports (i.e. struct)\n2) program dependencies (i.e. oslo_log)\n3) local modules (i.e. onasca_api.common.repositories.exception).\n\nTherefore you\u0027ve chances to imports are wrong and should be partially rollbacked to previous state in the manner described above.",
      "revId": "a17a313a76415598891b8bcb5abfdeeab05b6b5b",
